<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7497a87e-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s150903"><num value="150903">§ 150903.</num><heading> Membership</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id7497a87f-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s150903/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Eligibility</inline>.—</heading><content>Except as provided in this chapter, eligibility for membership in the corporation and the rights and privileges of members are as provided in the bylaws.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id7497a880-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s150903/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Voting</inline>.—</heading><content>Each member (except an honorary or associate member) has one vote on each matter submitted to a vote at a meeting of the members.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id7497a881-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7">(<ref href="/us/pl/105/225">Pub. L. 105–225</ref>, <date date="1998-08-12">Aug. 12, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/1395">112 Stat. 1395</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
